content:
You can now customize your backup schedule to suit your needs. Configure your policy to capture backups monthly, weekly, daily, or hourly. You can also choose a start time and preferred time zone.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise, Professional, and Unlimited editions.

Who: This change applies to editions that have the Salesforce Backup add-on subscription.

How: In the Salesforce Backup app, on the Backup tab, click Configure Policy Defaults. Then choose when you want the app to make backups.

Messages on the Logs page are simpler, easier to scan, and more informative. The Log Name column now shows only when jobs have started and complete. New job status categories group issues based on severity: errors that require help from Salesforce Customer Support, alerts about states, and informational messages.
title: Customizable Salesforce Backup Schedules
